◆ QDMI_DEVICE_MODE_T

enum QDMI_DEVICE_MODE_T

Enum of the device properties that can be queried.

Note
The values of this enum are meant to be used as bitflags. Hence, their values must be powers of 2.
Enumerator
QDMI_DEVICE_MODE_READONLY 

To open the device in read-only mode.

QDMI_DEVICE_MODE_READWRITE 

To open the device in read-write mode.

◆ QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_T

enum QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_T

Enum of the device properties that can be queried.

Enumerator
QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_NAME 

char* (string) The name of the device.

QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_VERSION 

char* (string) The version of the device.

QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_STATUS 

int The QDMI_Device_Status of the device.

QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_LIBRARYVERSION 

char* (string) The implemented version of QDMI.

QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_QUBITSNUM 

int The number of qubits in the device.

QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_COUPLINGMAP 

int* (int list) The coupling map of the device.

The returned list contains pairs of qubits that are coupled. The pairs in the list are flattened such that the first qubit of the pair is at index 2n and the second qubit is at index 2n+1. For example, a 2-qubit device with a coupling map of (0, 1) would return {0, 1}. A 3-qubit device with a coupling map of (0, 1), (1, 2) would return {0, 1, 1, 2}.

QDMI_DEVICE_PROPERTY_CUSTOM_1 

This property is reserved for a custom property.

The meaning and the type of this property is defined by the device.

◆ QDMI_JOB_RESULT_T

enum QDMI_JOB_RESULT_T

Enum of data-types of the result.

Enumerator
QDMI_JOB_RESULT_SHOTS 

char*(string) The results of the individual shots as a comma-separated list, e.g., "0010,1101,0101,1100,1001,1100" for four qubits and six shots.

QDMI_JOB_RESULT_HIST_KEYS 

char*(string) The keys for the histogram of the results.

The histogram of the measurement results is represented as a key-value mapping. This mapping is returned as a list of keys and a equal-length list of values. The corresponding partners of keys and values can be found at the same index in the lists.

This constant denotes the list of keys, QDMI_JOB_RESULT_HIST_VALUES denotes the list of values.

QDMI_JOB_RESULT_HIST_VALUES 

int* (int list) The values for the histogram of the results.

See also
QDMI_JOB_RESULT_HIST_KEY

Enumerator

QDMI_JOB_STATUS_SUBMITTED

QDMI_JOB_STATUS_DONE 

The job is done, and the result can be retrieved.

QDMI_JOB_STATUS_RUNNING 

The job is running, and the result is not yet available.

QDMI_JOB_STATUS_CANCELLED 

The job was cancelled and the result is not available.
